Follow [docs/design/01-art-phases.md](docs/design/01-art-phases.md) and [docs/art/pipeline.md](docs/art/pipeline.md). Readability: [docs/art/visual-vfx.md](docs/art/visual-vfx.md).

**Prompt workflow:** GLOBAL visual block → ONE asset-type block → ONE asset spec → GLOBAL negative block. One asset per generation request. Approve base design before animation strips.

**Review → production:** chroma `#00FF00` grid for review; transparent RGBA for runtime. No fake Persian text, logos, or watermarks in assets.

**Technical defaults:**

- Pivots: characters/towers/enemies **bottom-center**; projectiles/VFX/UI icons **center**.
- Animation strips: typically **8×1** per action; equal cells; no crop of limbs/weapons/tails.
- Maps: layered TileMaps (128×128 tiles); separable corruption/light/path overlays.
- Every production asset has a **stable asset ID** in `.tres` — never guess paths in gameplay code.

**Production gates:**

- **Phase 0:** Rostam style lock, prototype HUD, Khan 1 map readable at mobile zoom.
- **Phase 1:** four starter towers, jackal/boar/Lion, core VFX — before mass Phase 2–7 catalog.

Placeholders: `art/_placeholders/` until approved art lands. Organize under Heroes, Enemies, Towers, UI, Maps, VFX.
